{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":880,"text":"When someone mentions Cuba,"},{"time":2600,"text":"what do you think about?"},{"time":5200,"text":"Classic, classic cars?"},{"time":7280,"text":"Perhaps good cigars?"},{"time":9600,"text":"Maybe you think\nof a famous baseball player."},{"time":11720,"text":"What about when somebody\nmentions North Korea?"},{"time":14080,"text":"You think about those missile tests,"},{"time":16200,"text":"maybe their notorious leader"},{"time":18120,"text":"or his good friend, Dennis Rodman."}]},{"cues":[{"time":20640,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":22160,"text":"One thing that likely doesn't come to mind"},{"time":24520,"text":"is a vision of a country,"},{"time":26960,"text":"an open economy,"},{"time":28240,"text":"whose citizens have access to a wide range\nof affordable consumer products."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35240,"text":"I'm not here to argue how these countries\ngot to where they are today."},{"time":39880,"text":"I simply want to use them\nas an example of countries and citizens"},{"time":43600,"text":"who have been affected,\nnegatively affected,"},{"time":46840,"text":"by a trade policy that restricts imports"},{"time":49960,"text":"and protects local industries."},{"time":52480,"text":"Recently we've heard a number of countries"},{"time":55400,"text":"talk about restricting imports"},{"time":57600,"text":"and protecting their local,\ndomestic industries."},{"time":60640,"text":"Now, this may sound fine in a sound bite,"},{"time":63920,"text":"but what it really is is protectionism."},{"time":67160,"text":"We heard a lot about this\nduring the 2016 presidential election."},{"time":71600,"text":"We heard about it\nduring the Brexit debates"},{"time":74080,"text":"and most recently\nduring the French elections."},{"time":78680,"text":"In fact, it's been\na really important topic"},{"time":81440,"text":"being talked about around the world,"},{"time":83600,"text":"and many aspiring political leaders"},{"time":86040,"text":"are running on platforms\npositioning protectionism as a good thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":90800,"text":"Now, I could see why they think\nprotectionism is good,"},{"time":93600,"text":"because sometimes\nit seems like trade is unfair."},{"time":99120,"text":"Some have blamed trade"},{"time":101080,"text":"for some of the problems\nwe've been having here at home in the US."},{"time":104240,"text":"For years we've been hearing"},{"time":105640,"text":"about the loss of high-paying\nUS manufacturing jobs."},{"time":109560,"text":"Many think that manufacturing\nis declining in the US"},{"time":113160,"text":"because companies are moving\ntheir operations offshore"},{"time":116320,"text":"to markets with lower-cost labor"},{"time":118760,"text":"like China, Mexico and Vietnam."},{"time":122720,"text":"They also think trade agreements\nsometimes are unfair,"},{"time":126400,"text":"like NAFTA"},{"time":128120,"text":"and the Trans-Pacific Partnership,"},{"time":129960,"text":"because these trade agreements\nallow companies"},{"time":133440,"text":"to reimport those cheaply\nproduced goods back into the US"},{"time":137720,"text":"and other countries\nfrom where the jobs were taken."},{"time":140880,"text":"So it kind of feels like the exporters win"},{"time":144000,"text":"and the importers lose."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146960,"text":"Now, the reality is"},{"time":148200,"text":"output in the manufacturing\nsector in the US"},{"time":152080,"text":"is actually growing,"},{"time":153840,"text":"but we are losing jobs."},{"time":155440,"text":"We're losing lots of them."},{"time":157400,"text":"In fact, from 2000 to 2010,"},{"time":160120,"text":"5.7 million manufacturing jobs were lost."},{"time":164560,"text":"But they're not being lost\nfor the reasons you might think."},{"time":169120,"text":"Mike Johnson in Toledo, Ohio"},{"time":172080,"text":"didn't lose his jobs at the factory"},{"time":174080,"text":"to Miguel Sanchez in Monterrey, Mexico."},{"time":176560,"text":"No."},{"time":177800,"text":"Mike lost his job to a machine."},{"time":181600,"text":"87 percent of lost manufacturing jobs"},{"time":184920,"text":"have been eliminated\nbecause we've made improvements"},{"time":187760,"text":"in our own productivity\nthrough automation."},{"time":191720,"text":"So that means that one out of 10\nlost manufacturing jobs"},{"time":196440,"text":"was due to offshoring."},{"time":199680,"text":"Now, this is not just a US phenomenon."},{"time":202120,"text":"No."},{"time":203360,"text":"In fact, automation is spreading\nto every production line"},{"time":206720,"text":"in every country around the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209720,"text":"But look, I get it:"},{"time":211360,"text":"if you just lost your job"},{"time":212880,"text":"and then you read in the newspaper"},{"time":214560,"text":"that your old company\njust struck up a deal with China,"},{"time":217200,"text":"it's easy to think you were just replaced"},{"time":219680,"text":"in a one-for-one deal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222080,"text":"When I hear stories like this,\nI think that what people picture"},{"time":225080,"text":"is that trade happens\nbetween only two countries."},{"time":229120,"text":"Manufacturers in one country"},{"time":231560,"text":"produce products and they export them"},{"time":233520,"text":"to consumers in other countries,"},{"time":237000,"text":"and it feels like\nthe manufacturing countries win"},{"time":240040,"text":"and the importing countries lose."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243520,"text":"Well, reality's a little bit different."},{"time":247400,"text":"I'm a supply chain professional,"},{"time":249000,"text":"and I live and work in Mexico."},{"time":252520,"text":"And I work in the middle"},{"time":253800,"text":"of a highly connected network\nof manufacturers"},{"time":257000,"text":"all collaborating from around the world"},{"time":259160,"text":"to produce many\nof the products we use today."},{"time":262600,"text":"What I see"},{"time":263840,"text":"from my front-row seat in Mexico City"},{"time":266440,"text":"actually looks more like this."},{"time":269680,"text":"And this is a more accurate depiction\nof what trade really looks like."},{"time":274616,"text":"I've had the pleasure of being able to see"},{"time":276640,"text":"how many different products\nare manufactured,"},{"time":279160,"text":"from golf clubs to laptop computers"},{"time":282000,"text":"to internet servers, automobiles"},{"time":284600,"text":"and even airplanes."},{"time":286520,"text":"And believe me, none of it\nhappens in a straight line."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290440,"text":"Let me give you an example."},{"time":293520,"text":"A few months ago, I was touring\nthe manufacturing plant"},{"time":297800,"text":"of a multinational aerospace company"},{"time":300800,"text":"in Quer√©taro, Mexico,"},{"time":302920,"text":"and the VP of logistics points out\na completed tail assembly."},{"time":307440,"text":"It turns out the tail assemblies\nare assembled from panels"},{"time":311840,"text":"that are manufactured in France,"},{"time":314360,"text":"and they're assembled in Mexico"},{"time":316600,"text":"using components imported from the US."},{"time":320040,"text":"When those tail assemblies are done,"},{"time":322080,"text":"they're exported via truck to Canada"},{"time":324560,"text":"to their primary assembly plant"},{"time":326760,"text":"where they come together"},{"time":328040,"text":"with thousands of other parts,"},{"time":330480,"text":"like the wings and the seats"},{"time":332880,"text":"and the little shades\nover the little windows,"},{"time":335800,"text":"all coming in to become\na part of a new airplane."},{"time":339480,"text":"Think about it."},{"time":341320,"text":"These new airplanes,"},{"time":342800,"text":"before they even take their first flight,"},{"time":345400,"text":"they have more stamps in their passports"},{"time":347880,"text":"than Angelina Jolie."}]},{"cues":[{"time":350760,"text":"Now, this approach to processing\ngoes on all around the world"},{"time":354280,"text":"to manufacture many of the products"},{"time":356800,"text":"we use every day,"},{"time":359360,"text":"from skin cream to airplanes."},{"time":362520,"text":"When you go home tonight,\ntake a look in your house."},{"time":365680,"text":"You might be surprised to find\na label that looks like this one:"},{"time":370080,"text":"\"Manufactured in the USA\nfrom US and foreign parts.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":375160,"text":"Economist Michael Porter"},{"time":377360,"text":"described what's going on here best."},{"time":379840,"text":"Many decades ago, he said\nthat it's most beneficial for a country"},{"time":384600,"text":"to focus on producing the products\nit can produce most efficiently"},{"time":389000,"text":"and trading for the rest."},{"time":392000,"text":"So what he's talking about here\nis shared production,"},{"time":395520,"text":"and efficiency is the name of the game."},{"time":398720,"text":"You've probably seen an example of this"},{"time":401280,"text":"at home or at work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":403800,"text":"Let's take a look at an example."},{"time":405560,"text":"Think about how your house was built"},{"time":408520,"text":"or your kitchen renovated."},{"time":410600,"text":"Typically, there's a general contractor"},{"time":413080,"text":"who is responsible\nfor coordinating the efforts"},{"time":415320,"text":"of all the different contractors:"},{"time":416960,"text":"an architect to draw the plans,"},{"time":419480,"text":"an earth-moving company\nto dig the foundation,"},{"time":422440,"text":"a plumber, a carpenter and so on."},{"time":425000,"text":"So why doesn't the general contractor"},{"time":426880,"text":"pick just one company"},{"time":429520,"text":"to do all the work,"},{"time":430760,"text":"like, say, the architect?"},{"time":432600,"text":"Because this is silly."},{"time":434760,"text":"The general contractor selects experts"},{"time":437080,"text":"because it takes years"},{"time":438840,"text":"to learn and master"},{"time":440600,"text":"how to do each of the tasks it takes\nto build a house or renovate a kitchen,"},{"time":444400,"text":"some of them requiring special training."},{"time":448040,"text":"Think about it:"},{"time":449280,"text":"Would you want your architect\nto install your toilet?"},{"time":453320,"text":"Of course not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":454760,"text":"So let's apply this process\nto the corporate world."},{"time":458200,"text":"Companies today focus on manufacturing"},{"time":460800,"text":"what they produce best\nand most efficiently,"},{"time":464160,"text":"and they trade for everything else."},{"time":466680,"text":"So this means they rely"},{"time":469400,"text":"on a global, interconnected,\ninterdependent network of manufacturers"},{"time":474400,"text":"to produce these products."},{"time":475680,"text":"In fact, that network is so interconnected"},{"time":477760,"text":"it's almost impossible"},{"time":480080,"text":"to dismantle and produce\nproducts in just one country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484120,"text":"Let's take a look\nat the interconnected web"},{"time":486440,"text":"we saw a few moments ago,"},{"time":488120,"text":"and let's focus on just one strand"},{"time":490440,"text":"between the US and Mexico."},{"time":494640,"text":"The Wilson Institute says\nthat shared production represents"},{"time":497480,"text":"40 percent of the half a trillion dollars\nin trade between the US and Mexico."},{"time":503080,"text":"That's about 200 billion dollars,"},{"time":505760,"text":"or the same as the GDP for Portugal."},{"time":509720,"text":"So let's just imagine"},{"time":512280,"text":"that the US decides to impose"},{"time":515400,"text":"a 20 percent border tax\non all imports from Mexico."},{"time":519840,"text":"OK, fine."},{"time":521080,"text":"But do you think Mexico is just\ngoing to stand by and let that happen?"},{"time":526120,"text":"No. No way."},{"time":527840,"text":"So in retaliation,\nthey impose a similar tax"},{"time":530920,"text":"on all goods being imported from the US,"},{"time":534640,"text":"and a little game of tit-for-tat ensues,"},{"time":538200,"text":"and 20 percent -- just imagine\nthat 20 percent duties"},{"time":541680,"text":"are added to every good,\nproduct, product component"},{"time":545200,"text":"crossing back and forth across the border,"},{"time":547920,"text":"and you could be looking at more\nthan a 40 percent increase in duties,"},{"time":551280,"text":"or 80 billion dollars."},{"time":553800,"text":"Now, don't kid yourself,"},{"time":555600,"text":"these costs are going to be passed along"},{"time":557920,"text":"to you and to me."},{"time":561960,"text":"Now, let's think about what impact\nthat might have on some of the products,"},{"time":567240,"text":"or the prices of the products,\nthat we buy every day."},{"time":570600,"text":"So if a 30 percent increase in duties\nwere actually passed along,"},{"time":575040,"text":"we would be looking at some\npretty important increases in prices."},{"time":579640,"text":"A Lincoln MKZ would go\nfrom 37,000 dollars to 48,000."},{"time":584760,"text":"And the price of a Sharp 60-inch HDTV"},{"time":588800,"text":"would go from 898 dollars\nto 1,167 dollars."},{"time":594040,"text":"And the price of a 16-ounce jar\nof CVS skin moisturizer"},{"time":598200,"text":"would go from 13 dollars to 17 dollars."},{"time":602240,"text":"Now, remember, this is only looking\nat one strand of the production chain"},{"time":607640,"text":"between the US and Mexico,"},{"time":609040,"text":"so multiply this out\nacross all of the strands."},{"time":612600,"text":"The impact could be considerable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":614280,"text":"Now, just think about this:"},{"time":616960,"text":"even if we were able\nto dismantle this network"},{"time":621480,"text":"and produce products in just one country,"},{"time":624720,"text":"which by the way is easier said than done,"},{"time":627240,"text":"we would still only\nbe saving or protecting"},{"time":630680,"text":"one out of 10 lost manufacturing jobs."},{"time":633600,"text":"That's right, because remember,"},{"time":637400,"text":"most of those jobs, 87 percent,"},{"time":640080,"text":"were lost due to improvements\nin our own productivity."},{"time":643520,"text":"And unfortunately,\nthose jobs, they're gone for good."},{"time":648160,"text":"So the real question is,"},{"time":650520,"text":"does it make sense for us\nto drive up prices"},{"time":652880,"text":"to the point where many of us can't afford\nthe basic goods we use every day"},{"time":659280,"text":"for the purpose of saving a job"},{"time":661520,"text":"that might be eliminated\nin a couple of years anyway?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":666040,"text":"The reality is that shared production"},{"time":668080,"text":"allows us to manufacture\nhigher quality products"},{"time":671760,"text":"at lower costs."},{"time":673000,"text":"It's that simple."},{"time":674960,"text":"It allows us to get more"},{"time":676840,"text":"out of the limited resources\nand expertise we have"},{"time":679280,"text":"and at the same time\nbenefit from lower prices."},{"time":683560,"text":"It's really important to remember"},{"time":685640,"text":"that for shared production\nto be effective,"},{"time":688480,"text":"it relies on efficient cross-border\nmovement of raw materials,"},{"time":693920,"text":"components and finished products."}]},{"cues":[{"time":696960,"text":"So remember this:"},{"time":699120,"text":"the next time you're hearing somebody\ntry to sell you on the idea"},{"time":703200,"text":"that protectionism is a good deal,"},{"time":706440,"text":"it's just not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":708040,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":709280,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}